SIMPLE: lucubration
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lucubration
<hw>Lu`cu*bra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[l.
<ets>lucubratio</ets>;cf. F. <ets>lucubration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of lucubrating, or studying by candlelight; nocturnal
study; meditation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>After long <qex>lucubration</qex> I have hit upon such an
expedient.</q> <rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is composed by night; that which is
produced by meditation in retirement; hence (loosely) any literary
composition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy <qex>lucubrations</qex> have been perused by several of our
friends.</q> <rj><qau>Tatler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lucubrator</ent>⟦br⟧
